meta {
  name: Validate – File Upload
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/v1/validate
  body: multipartForm
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

body:multipart-form {
  upload: @file(../../../data/sales.csv)
}

docs {
  ## Validate – File Upload

  Upload a CSV or Parquet file for validation via multipart/form-data.

  - Accepted formats: `.csv`, `.parquet`
  - Max size: 10 MB
  - The suffix check runs **before** bytes are buffered — unsupported types
    are rejected immediately with HTTP 400.

  ### How to use
  Replace `../../../data/sales.csv` with your local test file path.

  ### Expected response `200` (invalid rows present)
  ```json
  {
    "file": "sales.csv",
    "total_rows": 10,
    "valid_rows": 7,
    "invalid_rows": 3,
    "is_valid": false,
    "errors": [
      {
        "column": "quantity",
        "check": "greater_than(0)",
        "row_index": 7,
        "failure_case": "-1"
      }
    ]
  }
  ```

  ### Error responses
  | Status | Cause |
  |--------|-------|
  | 400    | Unsupported file extension |
  | 429    | Rate limit exceeded (nginx: 5 req/s on /validate) |
  | 500    | Internal pipeline failure |
}
